---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="How I Lead with AI · Mollie Cox"
  description="An operating model, not a tool list. How Mollie Cox builds with AI as a co-founder, not a calculator."
>
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <!-- HERO -->
  <!-- ============================== -->
  <section class="case-hero-dark">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-20 md:py-32 relative z-10">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-cream/60 hover:text-orange transition-colors mb-16"
      >
        ← Home
      </a>

      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-6">AI Operating Model</p>

      <h1 class="font-display text-display-lg text-cream leading-[0.95] tracking-tight max-w-[22ch]">
        How I actually lead with AI<span class="brand-period">.</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-10 text-xl text-cream/80 leading-relaxed max-w-[48ch]">
        Everyone in 2026 says they use AI. Very few have redesigned how they work
        around what AI can actually do. Not a page about tools. A page about
        treating AI like a co-founder instead of a calculator.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-10 flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href="/work/course-code"
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-orange text-cream font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] hover:bg-orange-deep transition-colors"
          style="border-radius: 999px;"
        >
          See Course Code case study →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- The distinction (pull quote moment) -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="grid-backdrop border-b border-ink/10 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-top"></div>
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-bottom"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32 relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-8">The distinction</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-ink leading-[1.0] tracking-tight max-w-[24ch]" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5.5vw, 5rem);">
        AI as a faster keyboard is useful. <span class="text-orange italic">AI with real authority is something else.</span>
      </h2>
      <div class="mt-16 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 max-w-5xl">
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Most "AI-powered" workflows are autocomplete. Write a prompt, get a draft,
          edit it, move on. That's AI as a faster keyboard. Useful, but not
          transformative.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          The operating model I built starts from a different premise: what if AI
          had real authority, not just access? An AI with commit rights, assigned
          work, and a persistent identity is something else.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- THREE DOCUMENTS (3-pillar with linocut icons) -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The infrastructure</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[26ch] mb-16">
      Three documents run everything.
    </h2>

    <div class="pillar-grid">

      <!-- SOUL.md -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Heart with internal hatching = "soul" -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <!-- Heart fill -->
            <path d="M40 66 C 20 50, 10 38, 10 26 C 10 18, 18 12, 26 14 C 32 15, 38 20, 40 26 C 42 20, 48 15, 54 14 C 62 12, 70 18, 70 26 C 70 38, 60 50, 40 66 Z" fill="#E13D0F"/>
            <!-- Hatching texture inside -->
            <line x1="22" y1="30" x2="32" y2="40" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.6"/>
            <line x1="28" y1="26" x2="40" y2="38" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.6"/>
            <line x1="36" y1="28" x2="48" y2="40" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.2" opacity="0.6"/>
            <!-- Outer outline -->
            <path d="M40 66 C 20 50, 10 38, 10 26 C 10 18, 18 12, 26 14 C 32 15, 38 20, 40 26 C 42 20, 48 15, 54 14 C 62 12, 70 18, 70 26 C 70 38, 60 50, 40 66 Z" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-3">SOUL.md</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            Who she is.
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            My AI co-founder has a soul document. It defines her personality and voice,
            her values, her decision rights, and her relationship to me. Generic is the
            enemy of taste. SOUL.md is why her Linear comments sound like a person, not
            a status bot.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- AGENTS.md -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Scroll / agreement: rolled top edge, ruled lines inside -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <!-- Top scroll roll -->
            <ellipse cx="40" cy="14" rx="22" ry="6" fill="#E13D0F"/>
            <!-- Body of scroll -->
            <rect x="18" y="14" width="44" height="48" fill="#E13D0F"/>
            <!-- Bottom roll -->
            <ellipse cx="40" cy="62" rx="22" ry="6" fill="#02101D"/>
            <!-- Ruled lines (cream) -->
            <line x1="24" y1="26" x2="56" y2="26" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="24" y1="34" x2="56" y2="34" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="24" y1="42" x2="50" y2="42" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <line x1="24" y1="50" x2="56" y2="50" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="2"/>
            <!-- Outer outline -->
            <ellipse cx="40" cy="14" rx="22" ry="6" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <line x1="18" y1="14" x2="18" y2="62" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <line x1="62" y1="14" x2="62" y2="62" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-3">AGENTS.md</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            The operating agreement.
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            The governance document. Hard rules (nothing deploys without QA). Workflow
            rules (Linear is source of truth). Cost controls. Autonomy without
            governance is reckless. This is what lets me sleep at night while an AI
            has deploy access to a live product.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

      <!-- MEMORY.md -->
      <div class="pillar">
        <div class="pillar-icon">
          <!-- Brain / book hybrid: filled brain shape with hatching -->
          <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
            <!-- Brain main fill -->
            <path d="M40 14 C 28 14, 20 22, 20 32 C 18 36, 18 42, 22 46 C 22 54, 28 60, 36 60 L 44 60 C 52 60, 58 54, 58 46 C 62 42, 62 36, 60 32 C 60 22, 52 14, 40 14 Z" fill="#E13D0F"/>
            <!-- Hatching folds (navy lines) -->
            <path d="M30 24 Q 36 28, 32 34 Q 28 38, 34 44" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M48 24 Q 42 28, 46 34 Q 50 38, 44 44" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            <path d="M40 18 L 40 56" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
            <!-- Outline -->
            <path d="M40 14 C 28 14, 20 22, 20 32 C 18 36, 18 42, 22 46 C 22 54, 28 60, 36 60 L 44 60 C 52 60, 58 54, 58 46 C 62 42, 62 36, 60 32 C 60 22, 52 14, 40 14 Z" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
            <!-- Pedestal/stem (book-like) -->
            <rect x="32" y="60" width="16" height="6" fill="#02101D"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-meta">
          <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-3">MEMORY.md</p>
          <h3 class="font-display text-3xl text-ink leading-tight">
            The persistent brain.
          </h3>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-body">
          <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
            Every session, my AI wakes up fresh. MEMORY.md is how she remembers. Live
            product facts, hard-won lessons (what burned $400 a month in unnecessary
            API calls), team context, brand rules, the ship log. Memory architecture is
            a product decision.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-tagline"></div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Authority structure: two columns -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-cream-warm/40 border-y border-ink/10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Authority structure</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-16">
        What stays with me, what gets delegated.
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-8">
        <div class="compare-cream">
          <p class="eyebrow mb-8">What I own. Non-delegable.</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { what: 'Brand direction and voice', why: "Taste can't be systematized" },
              { what: 'Pricing and positioning', why: 'Requires market intuition and judgment' },
              { what: "Who we're building for", why: 'Empathy and values, not data alone' },
              { what: 'Aesthetic judgment', why: 'My eye is the product' },
              { what: 'Strategic pivots', why: 'Consequence too high, context too human' },
              { what: 'Anything public-facing I haven\'t reviewed', why: 'My reputation' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <div class="py-4 border-b border-ink/10 last:border-0">
                <p class="font-display text-lg text-ink mb-1">{row.what}</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted">{row.why}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="compare-dark">
          <p class="eyebrow-light mb-8">What she owns. Full execution authority.</p>
          <div class="space-y-4">
            {[
              { what: 'Feature development', why: 'Ticket to ship, full ownership' },
              { what: 'Bug fixes', why: 'Same workflow, faster cycle' },
              { what: 'Database migrations', why: 'Schema changes flagged for review' },
              { what: 'Analytics setup', why: 'PostHog dashboards, Sentry, event tracking' },
              { what: 'Email sequences', why: 'Klaviyo nurture flows, trigger wiring' },
              { what: 'Deployment', why: 'GitHub push to Vercel auto-deploy in 2 min' },
              { what: 'Full QA before every ship', why: 'Hard blocker. Nothing skips this.' },
            ].map((row) => (
              <div class="py-4 border-b border-cream/15 last:border-0">
                <p class="font-display text-lg text-cream mb-1">{row.what}</p>
                <p class="text-sm text-cream/60">{row.why}</p>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Three layers of AI -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <p class="eyebrow mb-3">The architecture</p>
    <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[24ch] mb-16">
      Three layers of AI in Course Code.
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <!-- Layer 1 -->
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="linocut-icon mb-4">
              <!-- AI brain / chip mark -->
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <rect x="20" y="20" width="40" height="40" fill="#E13D0F"/>
                <rect x="28" y="28" width="24" height="24" fill="#02101D"/>
                <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="4" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
                <!-- Pins -->
                <line x1="20" y1="28" x2="14" y2="28" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="20" y1="40" x2="14" y2="40" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="20" y1="52" x2="14" y2="52" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="60" y1="28" x2="66" y2="28" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="60" y1="40" x2="66" y2="40" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="60" y1="52" x2="66" y2="52" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="28" y1="20" x2="28" y2="14" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="40" y1="20" x2="40" y2="14" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="52" y1="20" x2="52" y2="14" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="28" y1="60" x2="28" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="40" y1="60" x2="40" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
                <line x1="52" y1="60" x2="52" y2="66" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-2">Layer 01</p>
            <p class="font-display text-2xl text-ink leading-tight">AI as co-founder.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-2">Development</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-4">
              My AI co-founder runs on OpenClaw plus Anthropic's Claude. Sonnet for execution.
              Opus for strategy. She has her own GitHub account, her own Linear user, API keys
              to every production system, QA authority, and deploy access.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Model split was a deliberate product decision. Opus for strategy is expensive
              but worth it. Sonnet for execution is fast and cheap. Subagents for isolated
              tasks mean no context bleed. This discipline reduced AI operating costs by
              roughly 80% from early undisciplined usage.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 2 -->
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="linocut-icon mb-4">
              <!-- Lightning bolt: intelligence flowing through product -->
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <path d="M44 10 L 20 44 L 36 44 L 30 70 L 60 32 L 44 32 Z" fill="#E13D0F" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="3" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                <!-- Inner hatching -->
                <line x1="30" y1="36" x2="38" y2="28" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
                <line x1="32" y1="50" x2="46" y2="40" stroke="#F4EFE5" stroke-width="1.5" opacity="0.6"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-2">Layer 02</p>
            <p class="font-display text-2xl text-ink leading-tight">Claude in the product.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-2">Intelligence</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-4">
              The Anthropic SDK is a direct production dependency in package.json.
              Claude isn't just how Course Code was built. It's running inside Course Code.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              The data extraction pipeline uses Claude to normalize and structure dress
              code data at a quality level no regex pipeline could match. The moat isn't
              4,659 courses. The moat is verified data plus a women's POV editorial layer
              plus a brand voice. Claude is what makes that scalable without losing quality.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Layer 3 -->
      <div class="lesson-card">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start">
          <div class="md:col-span-3">
            <div class="linocut-icon mb-4">
              <!-- Gear with internal teeth -->
              <svg viewBox="0 0 80 80" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
                <!-- Gear teeth as a star-like shape -->
                <path d="M40 8 L 46 14 L 54 12 L 56 20 L 64 22 L 62 30 L 70 36 L 64 42 L 68 50 L 60 54 L 60 62 L 52 62 L 46 68 L 40 64 L 34 68 L 28 62 L 20 62 L 20 54 L 12 50 L 16 42 L 10 36 L 18 30 L 16 22 L 24 20 L 26 12 L 34 14 Z" fill="#E13D0F"/>
                <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="14" fill="#02101D"/>
                <circle cx="40" cy="40" r="6" fill="#F4EFE5"/>
                <path d="M40 8 L 46 14 L 54 12 L 56 20 L 64 22 L 62 30 L 70 36 L 64 42 L 68 50 L 60 54 L 60 62 L 52 62 L 46 68 L 40 64 L 34 68 L 28 62 L 20 62 L 20 54 L 12 50 L 16 42 L 10 36 L 18 30 L 16 22 L 24 20 L 26 12 L 34 14 Z" fill="none" stroke="#02101D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="eyebrow mb-2">Layer 03</p>
            <p class="font-display text-2xl text-ink leading-tight">n8n for operations.</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-ink-muted mt-2">Automation</p>
          </div>
          <div class="md:col-span-9">
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Self-hosted n8n handles the automation layer that keeps the business running
              without manual intervention. Weekly health reports route from PostHog to Slack.
              Klaviyo nurture sequences fire on onboarding completion. Linear webhooks
              activate my AI co-founder when I move a ticket.
            </p>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
              Why n8n instead of cron jobs? Cost. Six daily cron jobs running through the
              main AI session were burning $400 a month at peak. Migrating to n8n isolated
              the workflows and got costs under control. Operational automation should be
              cheap and durable. AI inference should be reserved for work that requires reasoning.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Cost discipline (the part most skip) -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-cream-warm/40 border-y border-ink/10 py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow mb-3">Cost discipline</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-ink leading-tight max-w-[24ch] mb-12">
        The part most AI evangelists skip.
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-reading mb-12">
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">
          Running AI at production scale without cost controls is how you burn $13
          in one morning because a heartbeat cron started reading a bloated JSON
          file. I learned this the expensive way.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-12 gap-y-6">
        {[
          { rule: 'No new cron jobs without explicit approval', why: 'Crons compound. Each one adds a fixed recurring cost forever.' },
          { rule: 'Model split is non-negotiable', why: 'Sonnet for execution. Opus for strategy only. Haiku for fallbacks.' },
          { rule: 'Session hygiene', why: 'New topic, new session. Long sessions compound token burn exponentially.' },
          { rule: 'Subagents for big work', why: 'Coding over 50 lines or deep research gets its own isolated context.' },
          { rule: 'Root file size limits', why: 'Heartbeat files under 1KB. Root files auto-load on every session.' },
          { rule: 'Archive aggressively', why: 'Done tasks move out of active context. Ship log lives in reference.' },
        ].map((row) => (
          <div class="py-5 border-b border-ink/10">
            <p class="font-display text-xl text-ink mb-2">{row.rule}</p>
            <p class="text-ink-soft leading-relaxed">{row.why}</p>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <p class="mt-12 text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed max-w-reading">
        The result: AI operating costs went from unpredictable and escalating to
        controlled and predictable. The model split alone cut costs by roughly 80%.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- What changed (dark before/after) -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="bg-ink text-cream py-24 md:py-32">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10">
      <p class="eyebrow-light mb-3">What actually changed</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-display-md text-cream leading-tight max-w-[28ch] mb-16">
        The bottleneck shifted from execution to clarity<span class="text-orange">.</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 md:gap-16">
        <div class="max-w-reading">
          <p class="font-display text-3xl text-orange mb-4">Before</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-cream/80 leading-relaxed">
            Blocked on "how long will this take to build."
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="max-w-reading">
          <p class="font-display text-3xl text-orange mb-4">After</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-cream/80 leading-relaxed">
            Blocked on "exactly what do I want this to do."
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="md:col-span-2 max-w-reading mt-8">
          <p class="text-lg text-cream/80 leading-relaxed mb-6">
            Spec quality became the highest-leverage skill I have. When AI handles
            execution, every decision that stays with me became more consequential.
            I'm not reviewing PRs. I'm making brand calls, pricing decisions,
            positioning choices.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-cream/80 leading-relaxed">
            This is the counterintuitive truth about delegating execution to AI: it
            doesn't make your job less important. It makes it more important, because
            your judgment is now the actual bottleneck.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- =============================== -->
  <!-- Meta-point -->
  <!-- =============================== -->
  <section class="grid-backdrop overflow-hidden border-b border-ink/10">
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-top"></div>
    <div class="grid-backdrop-band-bottom"></div>
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 md:px-10 py-28 md:py-36 relative z-10">
      <p class="eyebrow-voice mb-8">The meta-point</p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-ink leading-[0.95] tracking-tight mb-12" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 5.5rem);">
        Stop asking how to use AI faster.<br/>
        <span class="text-orange">Start asking how to redesign the work itself.</span>
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <p class="text-xl text-ink-soft leading-relaxed mb-12">
          The question every product leader should be asking in 2026 isn't "how do
          I use AI to work faster." It's "how do I redesign the operating model of
          this business around what AI can actually do?" That's what I built with
          Course Code. That's what I bring to every product org I work in.
        </p>

        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a
            href="/work/course-code"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-orange text-cream font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.15em] hover:bg-orange-deep transition-colors"
            style="border-radius: 999px;"
          >
            Read the Course Code case study →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
